  <section>
    <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Avatar fallbacks:</strong> Always provide initials via <code>&lt;span data-fallback&gt;</code> as a fallback when images fail to load</li>
        <li><strong>Status indicators:</strong> Use <code>&lt;span data-status="online"&gt;</code> inside <code>user-avatar</code> to show user presence</li>
        <li><strong>Heading groups:</strong> Use <code>&lt;hgroup&gt;</code> for name + role pairs — the <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> inside automatically gets muted color styling</li>
        <li><strong>Semantic stats:</strong> Use <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> / <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> / <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> for stat label/value pairs instead of generic <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> / <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> elements</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive layouts:</strong> The sidebar layout automatically stacks on smaller screens when <code>data-layout-content-min</code> is reached</li>
        <li><strong>Sticky sidebar:</strong> <code>data-layout-sticky</code> works on <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;aside&gt;</code> within page layouts, not on <code>&lt;layout-card&gt;</code></li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Ensure avatar images have meaningful <code>alt</code> text and buttons have clear labels</li>
        <li><strong>Stats formatting:</strong> Use abbreviated numbers (e.g., 12.4K) for large counts to maintain visual balance</li>
        <li><strong>Empty states:</strong> Provide helpful messages when activity feeds are empty</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

